# gen122 (L7, gist) + gen123 (L6/L7, focused): reading comprehension over a read
# passage. gen121 digested the whole passage; gen122 answers "what is this
# about?" with the single central concept + the most salient sentence; gen123
# answers "what did you learn about X?" with the sentences about X. Both read off
# the same extracted propositions and the same salience computation — derived,
# never canned, so held-out passages and topics transfer.

> read: Mercury is a planet. Venus is a planet. Mars is a planet. Earth is a planet. Earth is a home. Pluto is a dwarf.
< Learned 6 fact(s), skipped 0.

# Gist: the central concept is "planet" and the most salient sentence is surfaced.
> what is this about?
< Mainly about planet: Earth is a planet.

# Focused: only the sentences mentioning the topic, in original order.
> what did you learn about earth?
< About earth: Earth is a planet. Earth is a home.

# Anti-impostor: a topic the passage never covers is admitted, not fabricated.
> what did you learn about saturn?
< The passage doesn't say anything about saturn.
